               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism, 9 works (a-i)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Collection of miscellaneous Persian and Arabic works on Sufism and doctrine, comprised of various tractates assembled from different sources of different dates. Volume not dated; items h (datable to the late fifteenth century) and i (datable to the late seventeenth century) are exceptional in their antiquity, whereas the majority of materials belong to the early nineteenth century. Variable naskh and nastaʿlīq hands. Loose paper wrapper (ledger labelled Acquittance Roll for September 1839, Calcutta), watermarked (initials VEIC, E WISE, no date); torn and stained. Lacks binding. Stamped foliation. Folios detached and unbound; cropped, wormhole damage, later repairs. Condition, extremely fragile. </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1166-item1">
                     <locus from="1r" to="24v">ff. 1r-24v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. </p>
                        <p>Collection of Arabic homilies for Sunni Friday prayers and selections of Qur’an sūrahs by an unknown compiler. 
</p>
                        <p>Defective at beginning and end. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. </p>
                        <p>Neat Indian naskh, with Persian comments in rough shikastah in red ink transcribed around main text. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1166-item2">
                     <locus from="25v" to="32r">ff. 25v-32r</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21692">al-Risālat al-vujūdīyat al-sharīfat al-sharīfīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21692">الرّسالة الوجوديّة الشّريفة الشّريفيّه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Ṣūfī treatise on the existence of God based on the properties of light by an unnamed author. </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1166-item3">
                     <locus from="32r" to="32r">f. 32r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item c. </p>
                        <p>Untitled extract from an Arabic treatise ascribed to Ibn al-ʿArabī (d. 638/1240). </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1166-item4">
                     <locus from="32v" to="34r">ff. 32v-34r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item d. </p>
                        <p>Extracts of a qiṭʿah poem from an Arabic treatise entitled <title>ʿAqlat al-mustawfī</title> ascribed to Ibn al-ʿArabī (d. 638/1240). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Further verses and annotations added in alternating bold and miniscule nastaʿlīq at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1166-item5">
                     <locus from="37r" to="41r">ff. 37r-41r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item e. Previously incorrectly labelled as item f by Levy. </p>
                        <p>Treatise on z̲ikr or the recollection of God through Arabic prayers and invocations, by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Arabic passages overlined. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21693">Barzakh-i Muḥammadīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21693">برزخ محمّديّه</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="6" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1166-item6">
                     <locus from="41r" to="47r">ff. 41r-47r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item f. </p>
                        <p>Ṣūfī treatise ascribed to Khvājah Muʿīn al-Dīn Chishtī Sijzī (d. 633/1236). </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_9423">Vujūd al-ʿāshiqīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_9423">وجود العاشقين</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656319.0x000001 viaf_115144814502949780076" type="supplied">Muʿīn al-Dīn Ḥasan Chishtī, 1142-1236</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656319.0x000001 viaf_115144814502949780076" type="supplied">معين الدّين چشتى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="7" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1166-item7">
                     <locus from="47v" to="48r">ff. 47v-48r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item g. </p>
                        <p>Excerpt of verses from an unidentified treatise ascribed to ʿAyn al-Quz̤āt Hamadānī, that is, Abū al-Maʿālī ʿAyn al-Quz̤āt ʿAbd Allāh ibn Muḥammad ibn ʿAlī Miyānagī Hamadānī, who was hung in 525/1131. 
</p>
                        <p>The text ends abruptly, leaving the ultimate couplet incomplete. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164659043.0x000001 viaf_96998098" type="supplied">ʿAyn al-Quḍāh al-Hamadhānī, ʿAbd Allāh ibn Muḥammad, -1131</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164659043.0x000001 viaf_96998098" type="supplied">عين القضاة الهمذاني، عبد الله بن محمد</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="8" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1166-item8">
                     <locus from="51v" to="83r">ff. 51v-83r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item h. </p>
                        <p>Account of the miracles ascribed to the Naqshbandī saint, Khvājah Naṣīr al-Dīn ʿUbayd Allāh Aḥrār (d. 895/1490), by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>The work contains many historically and socially noteworthy details. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Early naskh-nastaʿlīq hands in the late-fifteenth-century style alternating with a more developed nastaʿlīq hand (ff. 70v-74v, 76r-83r).
</p>
                        <p>Annotations in margins cropped. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21694">Risālah dar khavāriq-i ʿādāt</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21694">رساله در خوارق عادات</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="9" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1166-item9">
                     <locus from="84v" to="118r">ff. 84v-118r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item i. </p>
                        <p>Extract from the Persian commentary on the Arabic Ṣūfī treatise, <title>Risālat al-tasvīyat bayna al-ifādat va al-qubūl</title>, treating the unity of God, by the Indian Ṣūfī saint, Shaykh Muḥibb Allāh Ilāhābādī (d. 1058/1648). 
                        </p>
                        <p>The present copy places the introduction at the end (f. 108v). 
</p>
                        <p>Colophon at end not dated (f. 118r): completed by Muḥammad Iḥsān. Datable to the late seventeenth century. </p>
                        <p>Annotations and corrections in margins cropped in parts. 
</p>
                        <p>Fluent nastaʿlīq hand with Arabic passages in scribal naskh. </p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21695">Sharḥ-i Risālat al-tasvīyat bayna al-ifādat va al-qubūl</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21695">شرح رسالة التسويّة بين الافادة و القبول</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656445.0x000001 viaf_187568969" type="supplied">Shaykh Muḥibb Allāh Ilāhābādī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656445.0x000001 viaf_187568969" type="supplied">شيخ محبّ الله الٰه آبادى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
